{"ts":"2026-06-27T12:38:25.305Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"hbs0o9ut","input":{"summary":"### Summary of Investigation & Solution\n\n1. **Investigation**:\n   - Reviewed the existing codebase and verified the implementation of the `app/api/v1/documents` and `app/api/v1/documents/[id]` API endpoints, designed specifically for managing Document Metadata CRUD operations.\n   - Audited the underlying Mock Database model inside `lib/api-auth.ts`, validating user model, role boundaries, and access constraints.\n   - Identified and analyzed the test suite `scripts/test-document-apis.js` which verifies JWT-authenticated API behaviors.\n\n2. **Implementation Details**:\n   - **GET `/api/v1/documents`**: Supported robust searching, query filtering (`client_id`, `project_id`, `document_type`, `status`, `visibility`, and `search` query parameters), JWT validation, and multi-tenant security barriers (preventing client admins/members from querying other clients' documents or accessing `admin_only` visibility items).\n   - **POST `/api/v1/documents`**: Restricts document creation to GFF Administrators only, generates a sequential ID (`doc-XXX`), auto-resolves client names, and persists new entries in memory across hot-reloads via global storage integration.\n   - **GET `/api/v1/documents/[id]`**: Securely fetches individual document metadata, enforcing identical tenant isolation constraints.\n   - **PATCH `/api/v1/documents/[id]`**: Supports selective updates of metadata fields (like title, status, or version) for GFF Admins, while strictly validating input types and formats.\n   - **DELETE `/api/v1/documents/[id]`**: Restricts document deletion to GFF Admins only and ensures accurate in-memory deletion.\n\n3. **Validation**:\n   - Ran `node scripts/test-document-apis.js` which successfully compiles the TypeScript files and tests authorization (401, 403, 404, 200, 201 statuses) across adminis